sep=: Story Title
As a user, I should be able to see the map of the state on the state detail page so that I can immediately know where it is located from me.
As a user, I want to get to related parks from campgrounds
As a user, I want to be able to click a specific park and see its lists of associated visitor centers and campgrounds, so that I can plan my visit.
As a user, I want to get to related states from a campground
As a developer, I want to read a technical report of the website so I can learn how the site was built.
As a user, we should be able to see embedded social media feeds.
As a user, I want to be able to navigate between visitor centers and their corresponding parks/states, so that I can see which visitor center is associated with which park and states.
As a user, I should be able to see all the states when I click on States so that I can quickly see my available options when planning my trip
As a user, I want to see pages of campgrounds rather than all of them on one page so that everything doesn't bog down trying to load at once
As a user, I want to look at a specific visitor center and see its hours of operation, so that I can plan my visit.
As a user, I want to be able to click on About so that I can learn more about the website, how it is used, and get background on the creators of the site.
As a user, I should be able to see multiple campgrounds when I click on Campgrounds so that I can quickly look through my options.
As a user, I want to be able to click a visitor center and see a map of where that visitor center is located, so I can plan navigation.
As a user, I want to click on Visitor Centers and see a list of park visitor centers so I can plan out my visit.
As a user, I want to be able to click on a specific state from the states list so that I can get to the detail page of the state and get more information on it.
As a user of the SWEtravels API, I want to query for campgrounds and get back results
As a user, I want to be able to navigate to all the pages from the home page because I do not want to use a broken website.
As a user, I want to be able to click on States so that I can view all the list of possible states with parks that I could visit.
As a user, I should be able to see an image of the campground.
As a user, I should be able to click on a specific campground to view more information on that campground
As a user, I want to see a carousel on the homepage so I can navigate.
As a user, I should be able to click on Campgrounds to view a list of campgrounds
